snippet.title: Ed Sheeran - Sapphire (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Listen to 'Sapphire' now: https://es.lnk.to/sapphireID

"Sapphire was the first song I finished for Play that made me know where the album was heading. It's why I finished the recording process in Goa surrounded by some of the best musicians in India. It was an incredible creative process. I shot the music video with Liam Pethick and Nic Minns across my India tour earlier this year, we wanted to showcase the beauty and breadth of the country and its culture. The final jigsaw piece for me was getting @Official_ArijitSingh on the record, but it was a journey to get there and such an amazing day of music and family. Me and him have done a full Punjabi version of the song that will come out in the next few weeks, which has a lot more of him on it. This is the album version of the song, and my favourite song on the album. Hope you guys love it. Sapphire out now" - Ed x

snippet.description:
In Weekend Ka Mahabharat, the battlefield isn't Kurukshetra ‚Äî it's the living room! üè†‚öîÔ∏è
Prashant and Sayali, your favorite desi couple, go head-to-head in the ultimate weekend showdown. Prashant dreams of a peaceful weekend with snacks and sleep, while Sayali is all set with plans to go out, explore, and make "memories." What starts as a casual discussion quickly turns into a hilarious war of logic, drama, and emotional blackmail! üòÖ‚ù§Ô∏è

This sketch is every couple ever ‚Äî one wants Netflix, the other wants adventure. Who will win this Weekend Ka Mahabharat? Watch now to find out!

Dr Satish Kumar is a widely respected Pastor, Author, International speaker and Humanitarian.
 His powerful preaching, visionary leadership and Integrity have earned him much respect and following not only in India but around the world.

He is known for his emphasis on strong moral values, compassion and commitment to biblical standard of living. Despite his vast following and influence, Dr Satish Kumar remains a humble Man of God, who loves people and is accessible to all.

His commitment to integrity, transparency, and authenticity in ministry and life has earned him much respect both in India and around the world.

His extraordinary vision, leadership capabilities and unwavering faith have resulted in him building the biggest Church in Asia with more than 400,000 members.

Dr Satish Kumar is also a globally recognized figure featuring widely on various international platforms.

He has been conferred the Doctor of Divinity degree from ‚ÄòThe Dallas Baptist University‚Äô and the ‚ÄòMother Teresa‚Äô award for his service to humanity. He is also the Honorary Board Member of ‚ÄòMuseum of the Bible‚Äô Washington and also a Board member of CGI International, founded by Dr. Paul Yongi Cho, of South Korea.

He has been widely recognized for his humanitarian work, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic, where he organized hundreds of volunteers to deliver food kits to the needy and suffering. He has also been instrumental in various community service projects, such as free medical clinics, food distribution programs and retirement homes.

He is a much sought after international speaker, who passionately communicates God‚Äôs Word. His messages air on 300 different television programs each month in several Indian languages, reaching millions in India and around the world.

Calvary Temple Hyderabad was built in just 52 days, which is a remarkable achievement. It is now the biggest church in Asia with more than 400,000 members. The dynamic worship, diverse congregation, biblical teachings and supportive environment make it an amazing place to worship and fellowship. Calvary Bible college, Calvary hospital, and Calvary school are offshoots of Calvary Temple and provide much needed education and health care to all its members. Calvary Temple is beautifully built and is one of the major attractions in Hyderabad featuring in the ‚ÄòTop places to visit‚Äô on Trip advisor and other travel portals. Hundreds of people visit Calvary Temple every day to enjoy the serenity and the admire the beautiful edifice. You are invited to visit and worship at Calvary Temple Hyderabad and experience Gods presence and listen to His Word.

Dr Satish Kumar is a widely respected Pastor, Author, International speaker and Humanitarian.
 His powerful preaching, visionary leadership and Integrity have earned him much respect and following not only in India but around the world.

He is known for his emphasis on strong moral values, compassion and commitment to biblical standard of living. Despite his vast following and influence, Dr Satish Kumar remains a humble Man of God, who loves people and is accessible to all.

His commitment to integrity, transparency, and authenticity in ministry and life has earned him much respect both in India and around the world.

His extraordinary vision, leadership capabilities and unwavering faith have resulted in him building the biggest Church in Asia with more than 400,000 members.

Dr Satish Kumar is also a globally recognized figure featuring widely on various international platforms.

He has been conferred the Doctor of Divinity degree from ‚ÄòThe Dallas Baptist University‚Äô and the ‚ÄòMother Teresa‚Äô award for his service to humanity. He is also the Honorary Board Member of ‚ÄòMuseum of the Bible‚Äô Washington and also a Board member of CGI International, founded by Dr. Paul Yongi Cho, of South Korea.

He has been widely recognized for his humanitarian work, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic, where he organized hundreds of volunteers to deliver food kits to the needy and suffering. He has also been instrumental in various community service projects, such as free medical clinics, food distribution programs and retirement homes.

He is a much sought after international speaker, who passionately communicates God‚Äôs Word. His messages air on 300 different television programs each month in several Indian languages, reaching millions in India and around the world.

Calvary Temple Hyderabad was built in just 52 days, which is a remarkable achievement. It is now the biggest church in Asia with more than 400,000 members. The dynamic worship, diverse congregation, biblical teachings and supportive environment make it an amazing place to worship and fellowship. Calvary Bible college, Calvary hospital, and Calvary school are offshoots of Calvary Temple and provide much needed education and health care to all its members. Calvary Temple is beautifully built and is one of the major attractions in Hyderabad featuring in the ‚ÄòTop places to visit‚Äô on Trip advisor and other travel portals. Hundreds of people visit Calvary Temple every day to enjoy the serenity and the admire the beautiful edifice. You are invited to visit and worship at Calvary Temple Hyderabad and experience Gods presence and listen to His Word.

snippet.title: Ronth| Official Trailer| Dileesh Pothan, Roshan Mathew| Directed by Shahi Kabir| In Cinemas 13 June
snippet.description:
A gripping cop drama which follows a stoic senior police officer haunted by his past and his idealistic young partner assigned to night patrols. Their clashing personalities ignite tension, but as a series of intense and emotional events unfold, a reluctant bond begins to form. When a life-threatening incident threatens their careers, both must confront their deepest fears and darkest truths to survive the shadows of duty.


Genre - Drama

snippet.title: Kenny Sebastian - Indian Generational Drama | Stand Up Comedy
snippet.description:
The Crux of my special "Professor of Tomfoolery" is generations. How the differences affect our daily family lives. This part was such a journey in terms of writing it. It was fun balancing and covering all the generations while also doing justice to them. I had a blast observing the reactions from the audience during this part of this show! I hope you enjoy it and really excited to see how all of you feel towards the next parts that are coming out :)

_________________________________________________________

en-US.description:
Today I explored an old, deserted ghost village hidden in the middle of a desert. The entire village is empty now, but every deity, every street says something.
It seems as if time has stopped here... only silence moves with the wind.
This place is not just a location, it's a feeling - a little haunting, a little peaceful, and very mysterious.
Come with me on this journey of this lost world!

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: OnePlus 13s Unboxing & Quick Review ‚ö° OnePlus Made an iPhone?

snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. 

Are you ready for the challenge? 
Play now: https://gadaelectronics.page.link/dhgB  
#GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame

Watch the FULL MOVIE of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSk2_rPKNCDcjNAA8vaDN-E&si=rC5AotwLD2r3MHna

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Jheel Mehta / Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal / Monaz Mevawalla as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah / Dharmit Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku 
Ghanshyam Nayak / Kiran Bhatt as Nattu Kaka
Tanmay Vekaria as Bagha
Navina Wadekar / Monika Bhadoriya as Bawri

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Taarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

Witness the heartwarming story of brotherhood and family values in "Om Jai Jagadish." Released in 2002, this Hindi film beautifully portrays the lives of three brothers and their unwavering bond despite facing various trials and tribulations. When their father passes away, the eldest brother, Om, selflessly takes on the responsibility of caring for his younger siblings, Jai and Jagadish. As they navigate life's challenges, including financial difficulties and personal aspirations, their unity is tested. Will their strong familial love withstand the pressures of the outside world? Experience a captivating narrative filled with emotion, drama, and memorable performances from a stellar cast.

snippet.title: Uppum  Mulakum 3 | Flowers | EP # 316

snippet.title: BANANA BAJJI | Banana Fry | Valakkai Bajji Recipe  Cooking in Village | Tasty Plantain Evening Snack
snippet.description:
Today in our village, we made a delicious and crispy Banana Bajji using raw plantains, also known as Valakkai Bajji in Tamil. This traditional South Indian snack, especially in Kerala and Tamil Nadu, is a perfect evening treat, especially when served hot with tea. We sliced fresh plantains, dipped them in a flavorful gram flour batter seasoned with spices, and deep-fried them over a woodfire stove until golden and crisp.

Our village-style cooking brings out the authentic taste and aroma of this simple yet tasty snack. Watch how we prepare these bajjis in a natural outdoor setting, using fresh ingredients and traditional methods.

Enjoy the satisfying crunch and soft banana filling in every bite! Perfect for family gatherings or as a festive snack.
tags: how to make banana bajji at home

Enjoy the satisfying crunch and soft banana filling in every bite! Perfect for family gatherings or as a festive snack.

it.title: BAJI DI BANANE | Frittura di banane | Ricetta Valakkai Bajji Cucinare nel villaggio | Delizioso s...
it.description:
Oggi nel nostro villaggio abbiamo preparato un delizioso e croccante Banana Bajji usando platani crudi, noto anche come Valakkai Bajji in Tamil. Questo spuntino tradizionale dell'India meridionale, in particolare del Kerala e del Tamil Nadu, √® una delizia perfetta per la sera, soprattutto se servito caldo con il t√®. Abbiamo affettato platani freschi, li abbiamo immersi in una saporita pastella di farina di ceci condita con spezie e li abbiamo fritti su una stufa a legna fino a quando non sono diventati dorati e croccanti.

La nostra cucina in stile villaggio esalta il gusto e l'aroma autentici di questo spuntino semplice ma gustoso. Guarda come prepariamo questi bajji in un ambiente naturale all'aperto, utilizzando ingredienti freschi e metodi tradizionali.

Gusta la croccantezza appagante e il morbido ripieno di banana in ogni boccone! Perfetto per le riunioni di famiglia o come spuntino festivo.

id.title: PISANG BAJI | Gorengan Pisang | Resep Masakan Valakkai Bajji di Desa | Camilan Lezat Malam Hari d...
id.description:
Hari ini di desa kami, kami membuat Bajji Pisang yang lezat dan renyah menggunakan pisang mentah, yang juga dikenal sebagai Valakkai Bajji dalam bahasa Tamil. Camilan tradisional India Selatan ini, khususnya di Kerala dan Tamil Nadu, merupakan sajian malam yang sempurna, terutama jika disajikan hangat dengan teh. Kami mengiris pisang segar, mencelupkannya ke dalam adonan tepung gram yang beraroma dan dibumbui dengan rempah-rempah, dan menggorengnya di atas tungku kayu bakar hingga berwarna keemasan dan renyah.

Cara memasak ala desa kami menghasilkan rasa dan aroma asli dari camilan sederhana namun lezat ini. Saksikan cara kami menyiapkan bajji ini di alam terbuka, menggunakan bahan-bahan segar dan metode tradisional.

Nikmati kerenyahan yang memuaskan dan isian pisang yang lembut di setiap gigitan! Sempurna untuk acara kumpul keluarga atau sebagai camilan hari raya.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

‚ÄòBT' is a song about a rugged, tough guy drinking away his sorrows, his red, bloodshot eyes revealing a troubled past. Today, he's not to be messed with, as he is possibly missing an old love.


Artist : Vilen
Lyrcist : Vilen
Music : Vilen
Composer : Vilen
Director : Vilen
Screenplay : Vilen
Editor : Vilen
Colour correction : Vilen
DOP : Alex
Mix Master : Hanish Taneja
Music production : Vilen, Maniac
Recording studio : G10 Studio
Label : Darks Music Company
Starring : Vilen, BigSsmoke, Amit Om Malik, Akhil Rathee, Nitin Dabas
Location courtesy : Mnky Houz, Privee Delhi

Lyrics -
Ho ankh chadh ri ho ri kasuti laal
Laage se aaj gamm mai piwe se

Ho laage aa ri se sajan ki re yaad
Laage se aaj gamm mai piwe se

Ho ankh chadh ri ho ri kasuti laal
Laa ke peg 10 chaale sudha yaar
Laage se aaj gamm mai piwe se


Darr jaga chore ki re ankh dekh le
Makha ankh dekhle

Kisi laage se jalti aag dekhle
Makha aag dekhle

Laage se bhola aaj
Bhairav ka roop se le rhaya

2-4 bhaari bhaari
Gelyan yo bhoot bhi le rhaya

Chore hat hat ke chaale
Chori masta rahi se

Aaj suhaati na jo
Aankh matka rahi se

Aaja mardaan ke bhi halaat dekhle
Re halaat dekhle

Tadpe jo saari saari raat dekhle
Aaja raat dekhle


Ho iski kad pe jakham
Haath laal

Taare sir te jo aare se khayaal
Laage se aaj gam mai piwe se


Ho ankh chadh ri ho ri kasuti laal
Laage se aaj gamm mai piwe se

Ho laage aa ri se sajan ki re yaad
Laage se aaj gamm mai piwe se
